Requesting report from Facebook post about a pair wanted for theft in warehouse club. "???????????? ??????????????????: ???????? ???? ???????????????? ?????????? ???? ?????????????? Last week, these two men went shopping at a warehouse club on Atlantic Boulevard. They picked out new clothes before loading up their carts in the technology aisle: four TVs, a soundbar, and two Bluetooth speakers. Instead of bringing their carts to the checkout lane, they headed for the door, pushing past the employees checking receipts. They took their haul to a green Chevy Avalanche and put their stolen goods in the trunk. As they drove off, one of the TVs fell out of the trunk. District 2 officers responded to this theft and learned that the same suspects in the same vehicle had taken 5 TVs from another warehouse club in District 3 an hour earlier. Our investigation further revealed that green Chevy Avalanche has been used in multiple thefts citywide. Jacksonville, we need your help identifying who these men are. We want to remind them you actually have to pay for items you want; you cannot just take them. Plus, we want to know what they need all those TVs for. If you recognize them, call 904.630.0500. Prefer to stay anonymous? Reach out to First Coast Crime Stoppers at 1.866.845.TIPS. You could even earn a cash reward large enough to get a new TV (legally). Don’t know them? You can still help. Check out our Unsolved Crimes page, where we have dozens of suspects we need your help identifying. We’re just a few cases shy of identifying 500 suspects through our Unsolved Crimes page! ?? UnsolvedCrimes.JaxSheriff.org"
